Package org.cesecore.keys.validation

Interface Validator

  • All Superinterfaces:
    CertificateProfileAwareValidator, Cloneable, PhasedValidator, Profile, Serializable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    CertificateValidator, DnsNameValidator, KeyValidator
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CertificateValidatorBase, EccKeyValidator, ExternalCommandCertificateValidator, KeyValidatorBase, PublicKeyBlacklistKeyValidator, RsaKeyValidator, ValidatorBase
    public interface Validator
extends PhasedValidator, CertificateProfileAwareValidator, Profile, Cloneable
    Base interface for validators. All validators must implement this interface.

    $Id: Validator.java 28537 2018-03-21 12:21:25Z mikekushner $

      • setKeyValidatorSettingsTemplate

        void setKeyValidatorSettingsTemplate​(KeyValidatorSettingsTemplate template)
        Populates the sub class specific key validator values with template values based on ValidatorBase.getSettingsTemplate(). Sub classes only need to implement this method if they support configuration templates.
        Parameters:
        template - the validator settings template.

      • setNotApplicableAction

        void setNotApplicableAction​(int index)
        Sets the not_applicable action index KeyValidationFailedActions, defining what action should be taken when a Validator is not applicable for the input (for example ECC keys to an RSA key validator), i.e. #validate throws ValidatorNotApplicableException
        Parameters:
        index - the index.
